    "Html": "Thanks. This does work, but I'm wondering if there is a way to do this with a trigger on the checkbox instead. Obviously the difficulty would be in figuring out what to target. The reason I'm asking this is because I'd really rather have the checkbox bound to a boolean property in my data object. I think ideally, there'd be either a style trigger or data trigger that would change the column's cell style, while the binding would handle the data. Any thoughts?<br>\r\n",
